citeinfo.title: Township map of Qinghai with 2000 Census long form data (L7-L8)

descript.abstract: Township locations in Qinghai Province, China, with 2000 Census data from long form tables L7-L8 (9.5% counts). Includes introductory, employed population, and fertility information.
descript.supplinf: "The data is updated by end of 2000 year"

overview.eaover: Data categories are as follows. A) Population Emigration Information of the 2000 population Census data: L7-1, Population by current residence and place of birth. L7-2, Population by current residence and by time of moving to current township, town or street. L7-3, Population by current residence and type of emigration place. L7-4, Population by current residence and former residence 5 years ago. L7-6-1, Population by current residence, type of emigration place and education attainment (intra-region). L7-6-2, Population by current residence, type of emigration place and education attainment (inter-region). L7-7-1, Population by current residence, emigration place and occupation (intra-region). L7-7-2, Population by current residence, emigration place and occupation (inter-region). L7-8, Women having births by current residence, place of household registration and birth order (1999 11.l - 2000.10.31). B) Households & Housing Information of the 2000 population Census data: L8-1, Family households by use of houses, whether living with other families, single or multi floors, outer wall materials and by township. L8-2, Status of family houses by time of construction and by township. L8-3, Housing facilities by township. L8-4, Family households by source of houses and by township. L8-5, Family households by expenditure on purchasing or building houses and by township. L8-6, Family households by monthly housing rent and by township.

offoptn.compat: List of the 5th China Population Census Data Product Series. 1) The Completed Collection of China County/District Population Census Data Assemblies: The Collection includes more than 2,876 electronic books with more than 330,000 tables for all China 2000 county/district population census data assemblies, which provide extensive coverage at county, urban district and township levels. The data include rich information on general population, nationalities, marriage, age, education, occupation, housing, migration, etc. For more information, please visit: http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/census2000cnty.htm 2) The Completed Collection of National and Provincial Population Census Data Assemblies: The "Collection" includes all 32 China 2000 population census data assemblies with about 14,200 tables, which provide extensive coverage at national, provincial, city and county levels (see the list of all book in the attachment). All data tables are available in Excel files on the CD product. The users can use any web browser to browse the data by province. All table titles of the "Collection" are in both Chinese and English. For more information, please visit: http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/census2000prov.htm 3) The Township GIS maps with 2000 Population Census Data: The GIS maps include locations of townships (Xiang, Zhen and Jiedao), counties, prefectures, and provincial capitals, the county boundaries, the provincial boundaries, roads, rivers, and lakes. An online demo is available at http://gis.umdl.umich.edu/website/beijing/viewer.htm 4) The 2000 County Population Census Data with County Maps: The 2000 county data include 2000 county boundary GIS map and includes several other GIS maps. There are about 201 attribute variables integrated with the county map, including 170 population variables from 2000 census for counties and urban cities and 31 socioeconomic variables for each county. See details at http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/BookListDetail.asp?ID=1011 5) 2000 China Province Population Census Data with Provincial Map: The data include 2000 provincial GIS maps with more than 5000 attribute variables. See more details at http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/BookListDetail.asp?ID=1012 6) China City Statistical Indicators with Maps (1996-2001): This CD product includes a series of city statistical indicators with GIS maps from 1996 to 2001 with more than 200 variables. See more details at http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/BookListDetail.asp?ID=1255
